0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__articlePage","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Winterproof Your Deck: Maintenance Tips for Northern Virginia\",\"image\":[\"https://www.ldndecks.com/images/img54.jpeg\"],\"datePublished\":\"2026-04-21T04:00:00.000Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-04-21T04:00:00.000Z\",\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks Team\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\"}],\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/ldndecks-logo.webp\"}},\"description\":\"Preparing for snow and ice. Protect your composite and wood deck from winter damage with these professional maintenance steps.\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/blog/winterproof-your-deck-maintenance-virginia\"},\"isAccessibleForFree\":true,\"inLanguage\":\"en-US\",\"speakable\":{\"@type\":\"SpeakableSpecification\",\"cssSelector\":[\".leadParagraph\",\"h1\",\"h2\"]}}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgWrapper","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"src":"/images/img54.jpeg","alt":"Winterproof Your Deck: Maintenance Tips for Northern Virginia","fill":true,"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroImg","priority":true,"sizes":"100vw"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgOverlay","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerLarge","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__backLink","children":"← Back to News"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__title","children":"Winterproof Your Deck: Maintenance Tips for Northern Virginia"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__author","children":["By ","Loudoun Decks Team"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__divider","children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"April 21, 2026"}]]}]]}]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerNarrow","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentBody","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__leadParagraph","children":"Preparing for snow and ice. Protect your composite and wood deck from winter damage with these professional maintenance steps."}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"While we are currently in the heart of spring, the extreme weather cycles of Northern Virginia mean you should always be thinking one step ahead. The freezing winters of Loudoun County can be brutal on outdoor materials, causing wood to check and ice to expand in the microscopic crevices of your deck. Here is how you protect your investment before the first frost."}],["$","h2","1",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"1. The Fall Deep Clean"}],["$","p","2",{"children":"Before the snow hits, remove all organic debris. Wet leaves that sit on a deck over winter will rot and produce tannins that can permanently stain both wood and composite boards. Use a soft-bristled brush and mild soap to ensure no mold spores are trapped under the winter snowpack."}],["$","h2","3",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"2. Managing Snow and Ice Safely"}],["$","p","4",{"children":"This is the most common way decks are ruined. **Never use a metal shovel** on your deck surface. Metal blades will gouge wood and permanently scratch the capped surface of Trex and TimberTech. Always use a plastic shovel and push the snow *parallel* to the deck boards, not across the grain."}],"$L4","$L5","$L6","$L7"],"$L8"]}]}]}],"$L9"]}],["$La"],"$Lb"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"Jebrcr4Vyd2YosxlccnHN"}
4:["$","h3","5",{"style":{"marginTop":"30px","marginBottom":"15px","color":"#222"},"children":"The Salt Warning"}]
5:["$","p","6",{"children":"Be extremely careful with ice-melt products. Aggressive rock salts can dry out wood fibers and chemically degrade some composite polymers. If you must use a de-icer, look for \"calcium chloride\" based products that are labeled as safe for pets and lawns—these are significantly gentler on your deck’s finish."}]
6:["$","h2","7",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"3. Structural Integrity Check"}]
7:["$","p","8",{"children":"After a major freeze, inspect your ledger board and railing posts. The expansion and contraction of the ground can occasionally cause minor shifts. If you notice any \"play\" in the railing or new gaps appearing where the deck meets the house, contact the Loudoun Decks team for a professional maintenance check. A little bit of prevention in the fall saves a mountain of repair costs in the spring."}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__conclusionBox","children":[["$","h3",null,{"children":"Ready to upgrade your outdoor living space?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Contact Loudoun Decks today for a free estimate and planning consultation."}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/contact","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__ctaBtn","children":"Get Started"}]]}]
